@NODE 3. "Introduction"
                            Introduction.

	AmiBabel is a language translator. It translates text from one
	language to another using the translator server on altavista.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 0. "Getting Started"
                           Getting Started.

	Just double click on the AmiBabel icon. A Classact window should
	open on your Workbench screen.
	
	If you use a proxy, edit the AmiBabel.info TOOLTYPES and put
	your proxy host and port in it.
	
	If any required ClassAct classes are missing, AmiBabel will let
	you know and it will then attempt to download the latest classes.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 1. "Configuration"
                         Configuring AmiBabel.

	To configure AmiBabel, select the settings you will use and
	select "Save Config" from the pull down menu.
	
	AmiBabel will save all the data you last used, and window position.
	
	If you are behind a firewall and have to use a proxy server, then
	edit the icon tooltypes PROXY and PORT settings to suit your
	server.
	
@ENDNODE

@NODE 2. "Usage"
                          Using AmiBabel.

	The GUI is simple in design for ease of use.
	
	To translate some text to another language:
	
	o Select the language you want to translate from.
	o Enter the text you want translated.
	o Click on the Translate button.
	
	If all goes well, the translated text should be displayed.
	You can save the translated text to file by using the pull
	down menu option.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 4. "Requirements"
                            Requirements.

	Classact 2.0. (AmiBabel will download the latest classes if you
	               havent got them installed.)

	Internet account.

@ENDNODE

